    • Method Detail

      • check

        public static Set<Prerequisite> check()
        Checks if all prerequisites of WinguSDK has been met.
        Returns:
        set of all not met prerequisites. Empty set if every prerequisite has been met.

      • checkWithDefaultDialogs

        public static boolean checkWithDefaultDialogs(@NonNull
                                              Activity activity,
                                              int requestCode)
        Checks for prerequisites. If any of them is not met starts transparent activity that will ask user to grant all necessary permissions.

        Note that your activity will receive onPause() callback.

        Note that it is possible that user will not grant permission for bluetooth, or location. To make sure everything has been granted you need to call PrerequisitesChecker.check() method.

        As well if there is no play services available user will be prompted to download it.

        Parameters:
        requestCode - request code
        Returns:
        true if all prerequisites are met, false otherwise

      • resolveWithDefaultDialogs

        public static boolean resolveWithDefaultDialogs(@NonNull
                                                Activity activity,
                                                int requestCode,
                                                Prerequisite... toResolve)
        Tries to resolve given prerequisites. If any prerequisite is already met, it will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        requestCode - request code
        toResolve - prerequisites to resolve
        Returns:
        true if all give prerequisites are already met, false otherwise

      • getResolveResults

        @Nullable
public static ResolveResults getResolveResults(Intent data)
        This function helps check result of PrerequisitesChecker.checkWithDefaultDialogs(Activity, int) and PrerequisitesChecker.resolveWithDefaultDialogs(Activity, int, Prerequisite...). If any of mentioned functions returned false it means they started transparent activity for result. Using this function you can get result data form intent passed to Activity.onActivityResult(int, int, Intent).

        Remember that you should verify request code passed when called previously mentioned functions.

        Parameters:
        data - data returned by Activity.onActivityResult(int, int, Intent)
        Returns:
        data object containing both resolved prerequisites and ones that failed; null if no ResolveResults object is stored in intent
